  "source_id": "severe-childhood-obesity",
  "name": "Severe Childhood Obesity - Diagnosis Code Query (Pediatric)",
  "description": "**First pediatric phenotype.** Tests ability to find children with severe obesity via diagnosis codes. Pediatric obesity is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by severity level: parent obesity, morbid obesity, obese class II, obese (finding), and BMI\u226540 severely obese. The Synthea module restricts to pediatric ages (5-17 years). **The query MUST include a Patient.birthdate filter** (FHIR has no direct Patient.age search parameter) \u2014 without it, the query over-recalls adult obesity patients with the same SNOMED codes. Reference date 2026-04-28 \u2192 ages 5-17 = birthdate in (2008-04-28, 2021-04-28].",
  "prompt": "Find pediatric patients (ages 5-17) with a diagnosis of severe obesity, including the parent obesity concept, morbid obesity, obese class II, and BMI\u226540 severe obesity.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find children with obesity.",
    "broad": "Find pediatric patients (ages 5-17) diagnosed with any form of severe obesity \u2014 including the parent obesity concept, morbid obesity, obese class II (BMI 35-40), obese (finding-level), and BMI\u226540 severely obese (the most severe class).",
    "expert": "I need to identify pediatric severe obesity patients. The condition is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by severity: Obesity (414916001) is the parent disorder, Morbid obesity (238136002), Obese class II (443381000124105), Obese finding-level (414915002), and BMI 40+ severely obese (408512008). Search Condition resources for these codes. Note this phenotype is age-restricted to pediatric (5-17 years)."
  },
